# Write end-to-end (E2E) tests

- Cover top-N user journeys, not every screen—prioritize revenue / safety paths.
- Use stable selectors: `data-testid`, ARIA roles, text content—never CSS classes that drift.
- Wait on app state (network idle, element visible), not on `sleep` / fixed timeouts.
- Use a clean profile per test; reset auth, cookies, local storage between runs.
- Capture artifacts (screenshot, video, HAR, trace) on failure for triage.
- Treat flakes as bugs: quarantine, root-cause, fix or remove—do not retry until green.
